~bShell Commands~B

There is a group of commands for accessing the shell.  Following is the list:

    ~bKeys        Command         Description~B

    ~#uC-x `~U       insertPipe      Execute shell pipeline and insert its output
                                into current buffer at point, without moving
                                point if n == 0.

    ~#uC-x |~U       pipeBuf         Feed current buffer through shell pipeline and
                                read its output into current buffer (or another
                                buffer), with same options as "readFile"
                                command.

    ~#uC-x ~~~U       readPipe        Execute shell pipeline and read its output into
                                current buffer (or another buffer), with same
                                options as "readFile" command.

    ~#uC-x $~U       shell           Spawn an interactive shell session.

    ~#uC-x !~U       shellCmd        Execute a shell command and optionally,
                                display result in a pop-up window.
